  "prompt": "How much does an IFS officer get paid?",
  "response": "As of my last update, an Indian Foreign Service (IFS) officer's salary in India is structured according to the pay scales set by the Government of India following the 7th Central Pay Commission. The pay structure includes a basic pay along with various allowances. The starting monthly salary for a newly appointed IFS officer, typically at the rank of Assistant Secretary or Third Secretary, is approximately INR 56,100, excluding allowances such as DA (Dearness Allowance), HRA (House Rent Allowance), and others. \n\nAs IFS officers advance in their careers, their salaries increase depending on their rank and length of service. Senior positions like Ambassador or High Commissioner can earn significantly more due to their higher pay grades and additional responsibility allowances.\n\nPlease note that these figures are approximate and subject to change based on government revisions and additional factors such as location and specific duties. For the most current and detailed information, it's best to refer to official government publications or announcements.",
